1
00:01:00,119 --> 00:01:03,080
Episode 11

2
00:01:14,760 --> 00:01:16,599
Nanny Kong's lessons are finished

3
00:01:16,599 --> 00:01:18,480
and I found that they were quite productive.

4
00:01:19,599 --> 00:01:21,239
These last few days

5
00:01:21,239 --> 00:01:22,559
the three children have shown progress

6
00:01:22,879 --> 00:01:24,519
in prudence and composure of their conduct and speech.

7
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,279
That's good then.

8
00:01:26,879 --> 00:01:29,360
It means I did not invite her in vain,

9
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:32,199
and the energy was not used in vain.

10
00:01:34,559 --> 00:01:35,599
The three girls are idling around

11
00:01:35,599 --> 00:01:37,440
in the back courtyards.

12
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:39,279
Especially Molan.

13
00:01:39,879 --> 00:01:41,519
That child is most fond of poetry and literature.

14
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:44,480
I am thinking,

15
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,959
perhaps we should have them continue

16
00:01:47,959 --> 00:01:50,440
to attend Scholar Zhuang's classes.

17
00:01:52,519 --> 00:01:53,760
Is this your idea…

18
00:01:54,599 --> 00:01:57,319
or is someone pushing you from behind?

19
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:00,239
I just thought

20
00:02:00,239 --> 00:02:02,040
for the children to study more books

21
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:04,080
and understand more principles of the world

22
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:04,680
is a good thing.

23
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:10,039
You go back.

24
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:11,839
Let me think it over a bit more.

25
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:19,720
Yes.

26
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,080
Come out now.

27
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,240
Stop eavesdropping!

28
00:02:34,039 --> 00:02:36,160
How did you know I was eavesdropping?

29
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:39,039
You really want to return

30
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:40,919
to Scholar Zhuang's classes too, right?

31
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:45,800
Usually,

32
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,360
the sisters are idling together.

33
00:02:47,759 --> 00:02:49,199
Today we fight over clothing

34
00:02:49,199 --> 00:02:50,880
and tomorrow we fight over tea and food.

35
00:02:51,119 --> 00:02:52,360
Troubles arise easily.

36
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:53,639
It's better for us to all wake up early

37
00:02:53,639 --> 00:02:54,119
and go to sleep late

38
00:02:54,119 --> 00:02:56,320
to cultivate our writing and reading books.

39
00:02:56,559 --> 00:02:57,679
With our energies exhausted

40
00:02:57,679 --> 00:02:58,960
there's nothing left to fight about.

41
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,199
That's not untrue.

42
00:03:02,399 --> 00:03:04,320
But studying books

43
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:06,479
is not the duty of women, after all.

44
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:13,199
Grandmother, if you say these words

45
00:03:13,199 --> 00:03:15,559
your granddaughter must barge in here.

46
00:03:16,759 --> 00:03:17,399
Go ahead.

47
00:03:19,759 --> 00:03:22,240
You know what I think?

48
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,360
The saying that reading is useless is a lie.

49
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:26,160
If it's truly useless

50
00:03:26,160 --> 00:03:28,880
why do all the men of the world rush to study?

51
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:30,199
Can it be out of boredom.

52
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:32,679
I think the saying was

53
00:03:32,679 --> 00:03:34,080
simply an aspiration of men,

54
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:35,559
wanting women to be

55
00:03:35,559 --> 00:03:37,720
fools and docile forever,

56
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:39,919
so as to be easily manipulated by them.

57
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,559
I just knew you're a little clever thing

58
00:03:43,559 --> 00:03:44,960
and would understand it!

59
00:03:45,919 --> 00:03:47,160
That's not a false statement.

60
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,240
Not wanting women to study books

61
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,279
is short-sighted.

62
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,199
Dynasties and generations

63
00:03:52,199 --> 00:03:54,000
of women of great aristocrats,

64
00:03:54,199 --> 00:03:54,880
which one

65
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:56,720
isn't versed in books and principles since youth?

66
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:59,440
If it's true that it's useless for women to study,

67
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,080
then will they let their daughters

68
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,440
go through that suffering?

69
00:04:05,199 --> 00:04:06,399
Then Grandmother,

70
00:04:06,399 --> 00:04:07,839
your indecisiveness before Father earlier,

71
00:04:07,839 --> 00:04:09,240
it was fake too?

72
00:04:10,199 --> 00:04:11,119
You want Mistress Lin and Fourth Sister

73
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:13,800
to fret for a few days?

74
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:17,679
I want

75
00:04:17,679 --> 00:04:19,200
the mother and daughter to know

76
00:04:19,839 --> 00:04:21,279
that returning to the home academy

77
00:04:21,279 --> 00:04:22,320
is an opportunity not easily earned,

78
00:04:23,079 --> 00:04:24,440
so they know their place.

79
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,760
The Imperial civil service exam is approaching.

80
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:37,720
Everyone.

81
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:40,600
It's time to test your skills in earnest then.

82
00:04:41,079 --> 00:04:41,959
Today, I will use this

83
00:04:41,959 --> 00:04:43,480
”Sayings of Confucius and His Disciples”

84
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,359
as the foundation.

85
00:04:45,679 --> 00:04:46,959
I'll just flip it through carelessly

86
00:04:46,959 --> 00:04:47,640
and point to a line

87
00:04:48,279 --> 00:04:50,679
and we can use it

88
00:04:50,679 --> 00:04:51,760
as the topic of our discussion.

89
00:05:07,799 --> 00:05:09,040
How appropriate.

90
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,239
Everyone, listen.

91
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:15,640
Today's debate topic is . . .

92
00:05:16,279 --> 00:05:20,760
”To establish the eldest heir or to establish the most qualified heir,

93
00:05:20,760 --> 00:05:21,799
which is better?”

94
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,119
It's appropriate indeed.

95
00:05:28,679 --> 00:05:31,160
The hottest topic in the capital these days,

96
00:05:32,239 --> 00:05:34,640
is the succession battle

97
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,559
between Prince Yan and Prince Yong.

98
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:40,160
Scholar.

99
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:42,440
I fear this topic isn't appropriate.

100
00:05:44,239 --> 00:05:45,440
Not to worry.

101
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:47,399
Even an ordinary tea house in the capital

102
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:49,000
often discusses about this

103
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,480
as of late.

104
00:05:51,079 --> 00:05:53,679
With our doors closed and talking about it furtively,

105
00:05:53,679 --> 00:05:54,799
it's no worry.

106
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:58,880
As long as

107
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:01,359
you all do not leak it out?

108
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:10,000
Since Scholar says it's no worry,

109
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,239
let us discuss it then.

110
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,559
The current Emperor has no sons.

111
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:16,239
The high ministers are all urging His Majesty

112
00:06:16,239 --> 00:06:17,000
to adopt from the Imperial clan

113
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,760
and appoint him as the crown prince.

114
00:06:19,119 --> 00:06:21,559
Prince Yong is older but his qualifications are mediocre

115
00:06:21,559 --> 00:06:22,440
with no achievements to speak of.

116
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:23,519
His only asset is that

117
00:06:23,519 --> 00:06:24,799
he's got a horde of wife and concubines

118
00:06:24,799 --> 00:06:27,359
serving him day and night!

119
00:06:27,799 --> 00:06:29,320
He's exhausted himself from it

120
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:31,040
and raised a whole yard full of daughters and sons.

121
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,440
Second Brother. Watch your words.

122
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:36,480
We've got maidens here.

123
00:06:41,279 --> 00:06:43,799
Prince Yong is older

124
00:06:43,799 --> 00:06:44,679
and he has lots of children,

125
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:45,920
so it's appropriate to select him.

126
00:06:46,279 --> 00:06:47,519
What's there to battle about?

127
00:06:49,679 --> 00:06:52,839
Prince Yan is only half a year younger than Prince Yong.

128
00:06:53,359 --> 00:06:54,799
Though Prince Yan only has one son,

129
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:55,760
the father and son

130
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:56,959
are both intelligent and capable,

131
00:06:57,359 --> 00:06:58,399
and very much admired by people.

132
00:06:59,119 --> 00:07:00,880
To set a sage man like him as heir to the throne

133
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:02,480
will be a great consideration for the nation's future.

134
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:06,040
Half a year younger is still younger.

135
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:09,040
We can't surpass the order of seniority in age.

136
00:07:09,519 --> 00:07:11,320
It is not right, and it is not proper.

137
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,920
If everyone cares about talent only

138
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:15,320
then maybe it's possible.

139
00:07:15,679 --> 00:07:16,279
But everyone cares about

140
00:07:16,279 --> 00:07:18,040
ranking and stations.

141
00:07:18,559 --> 00:07:20,320
So that becomes a matter.

142
00:07:20,359 --> 00:07:21,839
Second Brother, you speak so easily.

143
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,239
This is the Imperial throne.

144
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,720
We're not talking about small households

145
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:25,640
fighting over a plot of land or a shop.

146
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:27,440
If we don't get the status clear,

147
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:28,359
that's causing chaos.

148
00:07:31,440 --> 00:07:34,200
Changbai, what do you think?

149
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:40,799
Sir.

150
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:45,760
Your disciple thinks the main eldest should be established.

151
00:07:46,119 --> 00:07:48,320
Emperor Qin deposed

152
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,079
his eldest son Fusu.

153
00:07:49,679 --> 00:07:51,519
It resulted in Qin Dynasty's collapse in its second generation.

154
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:53,320
Looking at the ancient times,

155
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:55,000
so many dynasties getting replaced.

156
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,559
So many met troubles after establishment of

157
00:07:57,559 --> 00:07:58,720
deposing the elder in favor of the younger.

158
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,000
That's not really true.

159
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,160
Emperor Wu of the Han Dynasty

160
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:04,640
wasn't the eldest, but after succeeding the throne,

161
00:08:04,959 --> 00:08:07,239
he was able to establish a flourishing nation

162
00:08:07,239 --> 00:08:08,200
and army that annihilated the fierce nomads,

163
00:08:08,519 --> 00:08:09,920
a lifetime of achievements.

164
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:13,160
So it shows it's not necessarily a bad thing

165
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,239
not to select the eldest.

166
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,359
But before Emperor Jing established Liu Che as the crown prince,

167
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:18,640
he first raised the birth mother

168
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:19,959
the beautiful Lady Wang, as the next empress.

169
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:22,079
So by law, it was just and proper.

170
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,000
So you can see,

171
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,000
Liu Che's ascending to the throne

172
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:26,959
is actually an example of selecting the main heir.

173
00:08:27,119 --> 00:08:28,279
Don't forget, Second Uncle.

174
00:08:29,079 --> 00:08:30,760
Emperor Hui of Jin,

175
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,440
the entire court knew he was a fool.

176
00:08:32,919 --> 00:08:34,919
But because he was the main eldest, he was still selected.

177
00:08:35,119 --> 00:08:36,159
And that is how the later conspiring of Empress Jia Nanfeng

178
00:08:36,159 --> 00:08:38,760
and the rebellion of the eight princes came about.

179
00:08:39,679 --> 00:08:41,559
If another prince had been selected to succeed him in the first place,

180
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:44,119
it wouldn't lead to the retreating to Jiangnan.

181
00:08:45,559 --> 00:08:46,679
How many idiots like

182
00:08:46,679 --> 00:08:47,799
Emperor Hui of Jin exist though?

183
00:08:48,239 --> 00:08:49,960
Do you think, Fourth Sister,

184
00:08:50,239 --> 00:08:51,640
that all the main line

185
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:52,640
of children are fools?

186
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:54,479
Just because the eldest

187
00:08:54,479 --> 00:08:55,400
from the main line isn't a fool

188
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:56,599
doesn't mean the second son

189
00:08:56,599 --> 00:08:57,919
can't be smart and clever.

190
00:08:58,719 --> 00:09:00,119
Emperor Taizong of Tang was not the eldest son of the main line,

191
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:02,039
but he still built a flourishing era.

192
00:09:02,479 --> 00:09:03,239
Examples of the younger son ruining the nation

193
00:09:03,239 --> 00:09:04,679
with his absurdness are many too.

194
00:09:04,919 --> 00:09:06,679
Emperor Yang of Sui is one.

195
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,440
He ruined a great nation

196
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,520
and that's common knowledge.

197
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:12,119
After listening all this time,

198
00:09:12,119 --> 00:09:14,359
why did the Young Lord and Sixth Miss

199
00:09:14,599 --> 00:09:15,840
not say a word?

200
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,840
Your disciple has yet

201
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,119
to make up his mind.

202
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,359
Yuanruo is the sole son of his family.

203
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:29,159
On the matter of selecting by age

204
00:09:29,159 --> 00:09:30,080
or selecting by merits,

205
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,200
perhaps he can't fathom it clearly.

206
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,479
That is indeed so.

207
00:09:34,719 --> 00:09:36,039
I think

208
00:09:36,039 --> 00:09:37,799
it's best to hear other people's great thoughts first.

209
00:09:38,919 --> 00:09:40,640
Sixth Miss,

210
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:41,719
selecting by elder or by merit.

211
00:09:42,479 --> 00:09:43,719
What is your thought?

212
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:49,559
I am just a girl.

213
00:09:49,559 --> 00:09:51,039
I've never thought of it.

214
00:09:51,039 --> 00:09:52,520
Just leave the nation policy aside.

215
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:54,840
Let's just say, hypothetically,

216
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,359
a small household,

217
00:09:56,359 --> 00:09:58,239
they have a useless elder son and a clever

218
00:09:58,239 --> 00:09:59,799
and skilled son from a concubine.

219
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:01,000
Which should be the housemaster?

220
00:10:03,359 --> 00:10:04,280
That's something the family master

221
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:05,400
needs to toil over.

222
00:10:05,799 --> 00:10:06,919
it is not convenient for me to speak wildly.

223
00:10:07,119 --> 00:10:09,000
Third Brother,

224
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,200
how do you now the eldest must be mediocre?

225
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:12,119
Maybe the concubine-born son

226
00:10:12,119 --> 00:10:14,200
is just a hollow embroidered pillow!

227
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:15,599
The second son being hollow

228
00:10:15,640 --> 00:10:17,280
doesn't mean the eldest isn't mediocre.

229
00:10:17,679 --> 00:10:18,159
You!

230
00:10:18,239 --> 00:10:19,359
I'm asking the Sixth Sister,

231
00:10:19,359 --> 00:10:20,520
why are you two arguing?

232
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:21,919
Sixth Sister, you speak.

233
00:10:23,919 --> 00:10:25,239
I don't know what to say.

234
00:10:26,599 --> 00:10:27,840
You must say something.

235
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,119
Say it.

236
00:10:29,799 --> 00:10:32,320
Let's not be hard on Sixth Sister.

237
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,640
She's young.

238
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:35,280
And she is not preparing for the Imperial civil exam,

239
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:36,760
so this topic doesn't have much to do with her.

240
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:38,080
Why should we press someone?

241
00:10:39,719 --> 00:10:41,200
I think,

242
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:43,359
we should hear out Sixth Miss' thoughts.

243
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:46,080
Though she is young

244
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,280
and she's not inclined to speak,

245
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:49,119
it's possible she might be wise

246
00:10:49,119 --> 00:10:49,880
and already made up her mind.

247
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:51,200
it's possible she might be wise and already made up her mind.

248
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:53,479
She's just watching us argue until our faces are red

249
00:10:53,479 --> 00:10:55,119
and laughing at us secretly.

250
00:10:55,239 --> 00:10:57,400
Uncle Gu, if you want to speak, just speak.

251
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:58,520
Why must you draw me into it?

252
00:11:00,359 --> 00:11:01,000
Second Uncle.

253
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,239
Why do you press her too?

254
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:08,559
The more you try to protect that little one,

255
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:11,080
the more the two elder sisters will bicker.

256
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:14,400
So let her handle it.

257
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:15,799
I think she can handle it.

258
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:16,400
No.

259
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:17,919
You don't know. Here.

260
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:21,599
In this house.

261
00:11:21,599 --> 00:11:22,919
She can't.

262
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:26,239
Very well. Everyone has spoken.

263
00:11:26,719 --> 00:11:28,760
Sixth Miss, you should talk too.

264
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:36,599
He's calling you. He wants you to talk.

265
00:11:38,039 --> 00:11:39,039
Hurry.

266
00:11:48,559 --> 00:11:49,479
Actually I want to ask

267
00:11:49,479 --> 00:11:51,119
Young Lord and Second Uncle Gu.

268
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:58,039
I am here. Just ask me.

269
00:11:59,359 --> 00:12:01,000
You two are both the legitimate heirs of your homes.

270
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,760
In discussing legitimate and concubine-born,

271
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:05,280
perhaps you both can speak

272
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:06,679
more freely than we siblings.

273
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:08,440
But today,

274
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,679
what I wish to ask is

275
00:12:10,559 --> 00:12:12,359
if both of you were to have

276
00:12:12,799 --> 00:12:14,919
a very accomplished sibling who is concubine-born,

277
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:16,840
how would you place yourselves?

278
00:12:17,919 --> 00:12:19,640
Who cares if it's legitimate or concubine birth?

